"{\"uid\": \"metro.co.uk-2024-07-30-coronation-street-emmerdale-olympics-schedule-shake-up-21326550\", \"text\": \"ITVbosses are giving soap fans an extra special treat as its soaps go up against coverage of theOlympicsin the TV schedules.  SoEmmerdaleandCoronation Streetviewers do not have to miss out on all the sporting action unfolding inParisover on theBBC, episodes of both soaps are dropping early on ITVX over the next two weeks.  On each day of transmission, fans will be able tostream new episodes of Corrie and Emmerdale from 7amon the platform.  To view this video please enable JavaScript, and consider upgrading to a web \\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tbrowser thatsupports HTML5 \\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tvideo  Up Next  A post on the soaps' official Instagram pages informed fans of the schedule shake-up -\\u00a0but they were also issued with a strict warning.  'We are giving you a little treat this summer whilst the Olympics are on,' the post read.  'But remember to keep this a spoiler free zone for those watching in the evening.'  A post shared by Coronation Street (@coronationstreet)  Both shows will still air in their regular slots on ITV1, with Emmerdale going out weeknights at 7.30pm, and Corrie following at 8pm on Monday, Wednesday and Friday.  Soap bosses similarly gave fans the chance to watch the soaps first on ITVXduring the Euros earlier this summer, as both shows were frequently moved around the schedules to accommodate coverage of the matches.  Meanwhile,EastEnders fans are facing continued disruption to their regular viewing, as the soap has been bumped out of its BBC One slot, instead airing on BBC Two at 7.30pm from Monday to Thursday during the duration of the Games.  Struggling with thinning or dull hair? Experts say the real issue starts at your scalp  Mother's Day gifts for new mums and mums\\u2011to\\u2011be under \\u00a350  The oral\\u2011care gadget making waves thanks to its powerful clean  Dunelm's new outdoor collection will get your garden spring-ready - from just \\u00a33  The exact blush Margot Robbie wore in Wuthering Heights and best budget alternatives  As ever, though, each episode will be available to stream on BBC iPlayer from 6am each day.  If you have got a soap or TV story, video or pictures get in touch by emailing ussoaps@metro.co.uk- we'd love to hear from you.  Join the community by leaving a comment below andstay updated on all things soaps on our homepage.  ArrowMORE:BBC slammed for 'cruel' and 'heartbreaking' interview with sobbing Team GB star  ArrowMORE:Olympic skateboarder claims 'moment of rage' came after cameraman ignored his warning  ArrowMORE:Olympics star screams in agony after suffering freak injury while celebrating medal win  Sign up for exclusive spoilers and interviews, handpicked by our Soaps Editor.  This site is protected by reCAPTCHA and theGoogle Privacy PolicyandTerms of Serviceapply. Your information will be used in line with ourPrivacy Policy  Sign up for exclusive spoilers and interviews, handpicked by our Soaps Editor.  This site is protected by reCAPTCHA and theGoogle Privacy PolicyandTerms of Serviceapply. Your information will be used in line with ourPrivacy Policy\"}"